parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belts can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: Seat belts do not hold in place
seat belts fail to buckle or lock
seat belts break or buckle failure
passenger side seat belt does not work
center seat belt does not fit a child safety seat
driver's seat belt no longer works.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair of Recalled Seat Belt Buckles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to repair recalled seat belt buckles in a timely manner can leave vehicles with defective seat belts on the road, putting occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Dealership does not have parts to repair recalled seat belt buckles
failure to receive parts to fix vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A clogged radiator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine, cylinder head, and other components, which can result in costly repairs and potentially cause a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: the radiator fan fails to turn on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed timing belt can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: the engine makes a loud noise
the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed cylinder head can cause the engine to overheat, lose power, or stall, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: the cylinder head cracks or warps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel tank can cause fuel to leak, leading to a fire hazard, and strong gas fumes inside the vehicle can cause health problems and discomfort for occupants.
symptoms: strong gas fumes inside the vehicle
no warning signs before the leak occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck or leaking fuel injector can cause the engine to stumble, stall, or cut off, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stumbles or hesitates on acceleration
fuel leaks from the fuel injector electrical connector.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear to brake pads and warping of rotors can cause pedal pulsation, leading to reduced braking performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Pedal pulsation when attempting to slow or stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system malfunction can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
Brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability to stop the vehicle.
